content:
A deployment is a place on your company's website that's enabled for Chat. Create deployments to implement Chat and control its functionality on your website.

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, Performance Editions and Developer Edition orgs created after June 14, 2012, Essentials, Unlimited, and Enterprise Editions with Service Cloud or Sales Cloud.

USER PERMISSIONS
NEEDED
To create deployments: Customize Application

IMPORTANT The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026. A deployment consists of a few lines of JavaScript that you add to a web page. Your organization can have a single Chat deployment or multiple deployments.

From Setup, enter Deployments in the Quick Find box, then select Deployments.
Click New.
Choose the settings for your deployment.
Click Save.
Salesforce generates the deployment code.
Copy the deployment code, and paste it on each web page where you want to deploy Chat.
title: Service Cloud: Creating Chat Deployments
